.TH poedit 1 "@PROJECT_YEAR@" "@PROJECT_VERSION@" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
poedit \- batch apply gettext \fBmsgid\fP/\fBmsgstr\fP mappings into \fB.po\fP files
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B poedit
.RI [ options ]
.RI [ po\-file ]...
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B poedit
reads UTF\-8, tab\-separated mapping data and merges translated strings
(\fBmsgstr\fP) for known \fBmsgid\fP values into one or more GNU gettext
.B .po
files, grouped by language. Prepare translations first, then use
.B poedit
to update catalogs in a single run; it is not a substitute for human or other
translation of the source strings themselves.
By default, target files are
.IR "po\-dir" / "lang" .po
for each
.I lang
in the input when that file is present. If
.I po\-file
arguments are given, only those files are written, and
.I lang
is usually inferred from the path (for example, \fB.../ja.po\fP for Japanese).
The built\-in
.B \-\-help
text explains a reasonable workflow, including for AI assistance.
.SH "INPUT FORMAT"
Each non\-empty line is split on
.B tab
(horizontal tab, Unicode
.B U+0009
and ASCII\ 0x09), not on space characters. Within each field, C\-\%style
backslash escapes are allowed, as in C string literals, so that embedded new
lines, tabs, and quotes can be written without breaking the TSV line layout.
The following layouts are supported:
.PP
.RS
.IP 1. 3
\&\fBThree\fP field layout: language code, then
.BR msgid ","
then
.BR msgstr ","
in that order, with
.B tab
characters between the fields. The first field is a Gettext language tag (e.g.
.BR de ","
.BR zh_CN ")"
and the two message fields are the untranslated and translated string.
.IP 2. 3
\&\fBTwo\fP field layout:
.BR msgid
and
.BR msgstr
only, with a
.B tab
between them, when a separate language code column is not present. The target
language is then inferred, in the following order: the
.BR \-l " " \-\-lang
value, the
.BR \-i
file or directory when
.B \-i
is a path, and the
.I po\-file
target name, depending on the invocation. That order matches the language\-\%resolution
rules printed by
.BR poedit\ \ \-\-help .
.RE
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-i " " \fIpath\fP ", " \-\-input=\fIpath
Read from a file or a directory. If this option is omitted, read the standard
input.
.TP
.BR \-l " " \fIlang\fP ", " \-\-lang=\fIlang\fP
Set the language for a single input file when a row does not start with a
language column.
.TP
.BR \-p " " \fIdir\fP ", " \-\-po\-dir=\fIdir\fP
Base directory for default \fBpo\fP paths (default: \fBpo\fP in the
current design).
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-dry\-run
Show the update plan; do not modify files.
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-verbose
Increase verbosity.
.TP
.BR \-q ", " \-\-quiet
Reduce log output.
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Print a usage message and exit successfully.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Print
.B poedit
version and exit successfully.
.PP
Further operands are
.I po\-file
paths to update directly.
.SH "EXIT STATUS"
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Error.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.BR LC_ALL ", " LC_MESSAGES ", " LANG ", " LANGUAGE
select the language of
.BI poedit " \-\-help"
and related diagnostics where gettext catalogs are installed.
They do not change mapping or
.B .po
file contents.
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.BR xgettext (1),
.BR msgmerge (1),
.BR msgfmt (1),
.BR gettext (1)
.SH AUTHOR
Written by @PROJECT_AUTHOR@ <@PROJECT_EMAIL@>.
